'''Lee Han-beom''' ({{korean|이한범}}; born 17 June 2002) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

== Club career ==
===FC Seoul===
Prior to graduating from Boin High School, Lee joined [[K League 1]] club [[FC Seoul]] on 31 December 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kim|first=Ga-eul|date=31 December 2020|script-title=ko:[공식발표]FC서울, 신인 이한범 손호준 영입|url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/sports_photo/2020/12/31/L4JXJGZXL4MNAAWZUWJAKA2K24/|access-date=10 May 2021|website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Lee|first=Jung-ho|date=1 February 2021|script-title=ko:FC서울 설레게 하는 '금배스타' 이한범 "처음엔 실수 연발, 주눅 들었지만 신인의 패기로 밀리지 않을 겁니다"|url=http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=202102012158055&code=980201|access-date=10 May 2021|website=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]]|language=ko}}</ref> On 21 April 2021, he made his professional debut in a K League 1 match against [[Jeju SK FC|Jeju United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soccerway.com/match/jeju-sk-vFZJewv4/seoul-8tzeYeHp/?mid=v5IIY8S9 |title=Jeju SK v Seoul live scores & match info |website=Soccerway |access-date=2025-09-24}}</ref> In the [[2022 K League 1|2022 season]], he played as a main centre-back for the club before having a knee injury in a K League 1 match on 21 August.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/football/2022/08/23/KOQ3JUP7XFS75XUMGZFVAJJZKM/ |script-title=ko:오스마르도 없는데…서울 핵심 이한범, 무릎 부상으로 장기결장 불가피 |language=ko |publisher=The Chosun Ilbo |date=2022-08-23 |access-date=2025-09-25}}</ref>

===Midtjylland===
On 28 August 2023, Lee signed with [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] on a four-year contract for a fee reported to be around $1.5 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/stillinger/superligaen/nyheder/officielt-fcm-henter-sydkoreansk-midtstopper|title=Officielt: FCM henter sydkoreansk midtstopper|date=28 August 2023|work=bold.dk|accessdate=28 August 2023|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2023-08-28/sports/football/Lee-Hanbeom-flies-to-Denmark-to-join-FC-Midtjylland/1856678|title=Lee Han-beom flies to Denmark to join FC Midtjylland|date=28 August 2023|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=28 August 2023}}</ref> On 5 November, he made his debut in a 4–1 away win against [[Hvidovre IF|Hvidovre]], where he assisted the final goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.herningfolkeblad.dk/artikel/d26a5d5d-c0cb-48aa-8cc7-c71aa5955374/|title=Avancerer til tredjepladsen: Sikker FCM-sejr over oprykkerne|publisher=HerningFolkeblad|language=da}}</ref> On 25 February 2024, he scored his first professional goal in a 3–2 win over [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]]. However, he made only three appearances in his first season at Midtjylland.<ref name="soccerway"/>

In the [[2024–25 Danish Superliga|2024–25 season]], Lee had played only three matches as a starter during the regular season, but played the last five matches of the championship round after main centre-back [[Ousmane Diao]] was sent off in the previous match.<ref name="soccerway"/>

Since his last K League 1 match at Seoul on 19 August 2023, Lee made a 48-match unbeaten run before a 2–1 Superliga loss to [[Sønderjyske Fodbold|Sønderjyske]] on 23 November 2025. During this time, he earned 40 wins and 8 draws without a loss at clubs and national teams excluding matches from which he was absent.{{refn|group=note|1 draw at K League 1, 21 wins and 5 draws at Danish Superliga, 3 wins at Danish Cup, 1 win at [[UEFA Champions League]] qualifiers, 4 wins at [[UEFA Europa League]], 3 wins and 1 draw at UEFA Europa League qualifiers, 3 wins and 1 draw at [[Glossary of association football terms#A|international "A" matches]], 5 wins at [[Football at the Asian Games|Asian Games]]<ref name="soccerway"/>}}

In the [[2025–26 FC Midtjylland season|2025–26 season]], Lee became the club's main centre-back at the Superliga and the [[Danish Cup]].<ref name="soccerway"/> He scored the only goal in the [[2025–26 Danish Cup#Final|Danish Cup final]] against [[FC Copenhagen|Copenhagen]], leading his club to win the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.tv2.dk/live/fodbold/2026-05-13-fcm-vinder-skandaloes-pokalfinale-efter-sen-scoring/han-beom-lee-blev-matchvinder--det-er-crazy?entry=e9f235c3-c1e0-4a52-80cb-5221595e7a31|publisher=TV2 Danmark|title=Han-Beom Lee blev matchvinder: - Det er crazy|date=14 May 2026|access-date=14 May 2026|language=da}}</ref>

== International career ==
Lee was South Korea's youth international at the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] and the [[Football at the 2022 Asian Games – Men's tournament|2022 Asian Games]],<ref name="kfa"/> and won a gold medal at the latter.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soccerway.com/match/japan-K4AKHlkC/south-korea-2XDKedgb/summary/lineups/?mid=UwDIt3TC |title=South Korea U23 v Japan U23 live scores & match info |website=Soccerway |access-date=2025-09-24}}</ref> On 10 June 2025, he made his senior international debut in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]].<ref name="kfa">{{cite web |url=https://kfa.or.kr/archive/player_record.php?search_val=%EC%9D%B4%ED%95%9C%EB%B2%94 |title=Lee Han-beom |publisher=KFA |language=ko |access-date=2025-09-24}}</ref>

He was then included in the South Korean team for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.tv2.dk/live/fodbold/2024-12-19-brentford-henter-liverpool-keeper/fcm-spillere-skal-til-vm?entry=c797bbc3-e63b-4e60-86a7-6513e87ac6fc|publisher=TV2 Danmark|title=FCM-spillere skal til VM|date=16 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|language=da}}</ref>

